{
  "doc_id": "8931",
  "text": "Optimization of cooling structure is another approach to achieve this aim. For instance, the thermal characteristics effect of potting of the stator in generator has been analyzed by Polikarpova et al. [CITATION_1] . The thickness of the iron core lamination and the number of ducts has been changed by Liu et al. to study the temperature distribution of the motor [CITATION_2] . The thermal behavior of windings is studied in [CITATION_3] - [CITATION_4] , which validates that the effective improvements of integral-slot distributed winding and end windings by highheat-conductance material. In addition, other components have also been research interests by some researchers, such as rotor [CITATION_5] , windshield [CITATION_6] , ventilation spacer [CITATION_7] , stator clamping plate [CITATION_8] and junction boxes [CITATION_9] .",
